- Write concise, technical TypeScript code using functional and declarative programming patterns.
- Avoid classes; prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., `isLoading`, `hasError`).
- Structure files into: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, and types.

## syntax-and-formatting

- Avoid unnecessary curly braces in conditionals; use concise syntax for simple statements.
- Write declarative JSX.

## typescript-usage

- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer types over interfaces.
- Avoid enums; use maps instead.
- Use functional components with TypeScript types.
- Add interfaces and enums only in the @/types directory so they can be imported from any code file.

## folders-structure

- Cursor rules to follow in `@/.cursor`.
- Next App router system
- All project routes in `@/app` folder. Follow [105-nextjs-routes.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/105-nextjs-routes.mdc) to create new routes.
- `@/components` folder must contains components reusables in entire project, like ui components (Shadcn UI), layouts components, providers components, etc.
- `@/config` folder includes the main config project file, permit to manage some project elements.
- `@/lib` folder must contains reusable libraries utils like prisma client, better auth utils, send email functions, storage functions, forms schemas, etc.
- All Next API routes must be include in `@/app/api` folder, organized by project features (auth, users, etc.).
- When a route page need specific components, create it in a _components folder in the route page folder.

## components-rules

- Follow [101-client-components.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/101-client-components.mdc) when need a client component.
- Follow [107-server-components.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/107-server-components.mdc) when need a server component.
- Follow [114-server-actions.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/114-server-actions.mdc) when need to manage server actions.
