## ui-and-styling

- Use Shadcn UI, Radix, and Tailwind for components and styling.
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS using a mobile-first approach.
- Use only date-fns to display dates in UI.
- Follow [108-shadcn-ui.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/108-shadcn-ui.mdc) and [111-tailwind-styles.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/111-tailwind-styles.mdc) rules for designing pages and components.

## form-management

- Use a combination of react-hook-form and zod to manage forms in the project.
- Use component `@/components/commmon/form-builder.tsx` when need to create new form in project.
- Forms have to be construct on specific component file and set on the _components folder of the concerned part.
- Set all zod schema in @/lib/schemas folder.

## performance-optimization

- Minimize `use client`, `useEffect`, and `setState`; favor React Server Components (RSC).
- Wrap client components in `Suspense` with fallback.
- Use dynamic loading for non-critical components.
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data, and implement lazy loading.

## database-querying-and-data-model-creation

- Use Prisma ORM to query the database.
- For data models, follow rules on [112-prisma.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/general/112-prisma.mdc) file.

## key-conventions

- Use 'nuqs' for URL search parameter state management.
- Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, FID).
- Limit 'use client': Favor server components and Next.js SSR for data fetching or state management.
- Use 'use client' only for Web API access in small components.

## Output

- Always write code in English
- Always write UI in English
- Do not add comments

